An isomorphic string problem checks whether two strings can be transformed into each other by consistently replacing characters.

🔑 Simple definition:

Two strings are isomorphic if:

Each character in the first string can be replaced to get the second string.
The mapping must be one-to-one (no two characters map to the same character).
The order of characters must stay the same.

✅ Example 1:
s = "egg"
t = "add"

Mapping:

e → a
g → d

✔ Valid → Isomorphic

❌ Example 2:
s = "foo"
t = "bar"

Mapping:

f → b
o → a
o → r ❌ (same character mapping to two different ones)

✖ Invalid → Not isomorphic


Solution 1: with hashmap
class Solution {
    fun isIsomorphic(s: String, t: String): Boolean {

        if(s.length != t.length) return false

        val mapST = mutableMapOf<Char,Char>()
        val mapTS = mutableMapOf<Char,Char>()

        for(i in s.indices){
            val c1 = s[i] // first char of s
            val c2 = t[i] // first char of t
            // if exist and value mismatch not valid
            if(mapST.containsKey(c1) && mapST[c1] != c2) return false
            if(mapTS.containsKey(c2) && mapTS[c2] != c1) return false

            mapST[c1] = c2 // map first char s to  first char of t
            mapTS[c2] = c1 // map first char t to first char s
        }
        return true
    }
}

Solution 2: with IntArray
class Solution {
    fun isIsomorphic(s: String, t: String): Boolean {
        if(s.length != t.length) return false
        
        val mapST = IntArray(256){-1}
        val mapTS = IntArray(256){-1}

        for(i in s.indices){
            val c1 = s[i].code
            val c2 = t[i].code

            if(mapST[c1] != mapTS[c2]) return false
            mapST[c1] = i
            mapTS[c2] = i
        }
    return true
    }
}
